#
# 0001 ngsi receiver --help
#
ngsi receiver --help

```
NAME:
   ngsi receiver - notification receiver

USAGE:
   ngsi receiver [command options] [arguments...]

CATEGORY:
   CONVENIENCE

OPTIONS:
   --host value, -h value  host for receiver (default: "0.0.0.0")
   --port value, -p value  port for receiver (default: "1028")
   --url value, -u value   url for receiver (default: "/")
   --pretty, -P            pretty format (default: false)
   --https, -s             start in https (default: false)
   --key value, -k value   key file (only needed if https is enabled)
   --cert value, -c value  cert file (only needed if https is enabled)
   --verbose, -v           verbose (default: false)
   --header                print receive header (default: false)
   --help                  show help (default: false)
   
```
